csv - emit loop or archive data in comma-separated-value format
Copyright 2015-2021 Matthew Wall
Distributed under terms of the GPLv3

This service will emit either loop or archive data from weewx in CSV format.
Typically this would be done using a template and the Cheetah reporting engine
in weewx.  But this service provides the option of emitting loop data, not just
archive data.

===============================================================================
Installation

1) download

  wget -O weewx-csv.zip https://github.com/matthewwall/weewx-csv/archive/master.zip

2) run the installer:

wee_extension --install weewx-csv.zip

3) restart weewx:

sudo /etc/init.d/weewx stop
sudo /etc/init.d/weewx start


===============================================================================
Configuration

The service recognizes a few options, including:

binding

  Indicates which data to emit, either 'loop' or 'archive'.  Default is 'loop'.

header

  Determines whether a commented header will be included as the first line of
  the file.  Default is True.

mode

  Determines whether the file will be overwritten or appended.
  Default is 'append'.  Any other value will overwrite.

filename

  Use the filename option to indicate where the CSV data should be saved.
  The default location for CSV output is /var/tmp/data.csv

append_datestamp

  When set to True, the filename will be extended with a date stamp.
  Default is True.

datestamp_format

  Format for the datestamp extension.  Default is '%Y-%m'

timestamp_format

  Format for timestamps in the CSV data.  Default is None.


===============================================================================
Examples

[CSV]
    filename = /tmp/weewx-data.csv
    header = False

